Park Su-jin.

255
00:15:48,761 --> 00:15:49,595
Here.

256
00:15:50,429 --> 00:15:51,805
Park Ji-hye.

257
00:15:52,931 --> 00:15:54,349
Park Chae-won.

258
00:15:56,894 --> 00:15:58,729
<i>Thanks to you,</i>

259
00:15:58,812 --> 00:16:01,065
<i>I've hit 500,000 followers.</i>

260
00:16:01,607 --> 00:16:02,858
<i>Thank you so much.</i>

261
00:16:18,457 --> 00:16:23,587
As you can see,
she seems to be a very popular influencer.

262
00:16:23,670 --> 00:16:26,715
Don't you think this might cause trouble
if we get involved?

263
00:16:27,299 --> 00:16:28,425
That's more work for us.

264
00:16:28,509 --> 00:16:29,760
Don't worry about that.

265
00:16:29,843 --> 00:16:32,638
Minister Choi has agreed
to take full responsibility.

266
00:16:32,721 --> 00:16:33,680
I see.

267
00:16:33,764 --> 00:16:36,433
600,000 followers.

268
00:16:36,934 --> 00:16:37,935
You punk…

269
00:16:40,687 --> 00:16:42,856
Do it! Of course we should do it!

270
00:16:43,357 --> 00:16:45,859
Whether 600,000 or six million,
we must do what we must.

271
00:16:46,485 --> 00:16:47,611
That's right! Do it!

272
00:16:47,694 --> 00:16:49,029
Deputy Bong, get ready too.

273
00:16:49,113 --> 00:16:51,281
What's my role this time around?

274
00:16:51,365 --> 00:16:54,451
Why do you even ask?
Obviously, you'll go undercover as a girl.

275
00:16:55,035 --> 00:16:57,287
What? Are you serious?

276
00:17:06,505 --> 00:17:08,632
Why are you taking it so seriously?

277
00:17:10,175 --> 00:17:11,969
Am I really dressing up as a girl?

278
00:17:12,052 --> 00:17:13,554
If so, would you?

279
00:17:14,346 --> 00:17:15,722
Why even consider it?

280
00:17:17,349 --> 00:17:18,934
Deputy Bong, provide backup.

281
00:17:19,852 --> 00:17:21,854
Inspector Na, get out into the field now.

282
00:17:21,937 --> 00:17:23,397
It won't be me this time.

283
00:17:23,480 --> 00:17:25,774
Who else, then?
You're the only inspector we have.

284
00:17:25,858 --> 00:17:27,317
I've hired a new one.

285
00:17:29,278 --> 00:17:33,949
<i>She's perfect for this case,</i>
<i>so why don't you just see how she does?</i>

286
00:17:40,831 --> 00:17:44,168
Ta-da! I drew Ye-ri. What do you think?
Looks like her, doesn't it?

287
00:17:44,251 --> 00:17:48,797
By the way, everyone,
So-yeong keeps insisting I'm like a cat.

288
00:17:48,881 --> 00:17:53,427
This is Ms. Im Han-rim,
our student teacher here for training.

289
00:17:55,345 --> 00:17:57,264
-Please introduce yourself.
-Okay.

290
00:17:58,265 --> 00:17:59,516
Hello.

291
00:17:59,600 --> 00:18:03,020
My name is Im Han-rim, and I teach math.

292
00:18:03,103 --> 00:18:05,689
Depending on how you all behave,

293
00:18:05,772 --> 00:18:07,649
I can become an angel,

294
00:18:07,733 --> 00:18:09,776
or I can become a devil.

295
00:18:09,860 --> 00:18:11,278
I hope we get along well.

296
00:18:14,489 --> 00:18:16,241
I'll take attendance.

297
00:18:16,992 --> 00:18:17,993
Kang Da-yeon.

298
00:18:18,493 --> 00:18:20,162
Kim Ye-rin.

299
00:18:20,746 --> 00:18:23,498
I don't think the front teeth
look the same.

300
00:18:23,582 --> 00:18:25,792
-No, they do.
-Don't they look the same?

301
00:18:25,876 --> 00:18:29,421
Guys, they're selecting uniform models
from Soyeon Girls' High this time.

302
00:18:29,504 --> 00:18:31,256
Our uniform is particularly pretty.

303
00:18:34,301 --> 00:18:36,428
No, I'm completely asymmetrical.

304
00:18:36,511 --> 00:18:38,722
I just always film my left side,

305
00:18:38,805 --> 00:18:40,766
but if I move the camera to my right…

306
00:18:49,900 --> 00:18:50,734
Miss.

307
00:18:51,443 --> 00:18:52,277
Yes?

308
00:18:52,986 --> 00:18:53,987
Ms. Im.

309
00:18:54,613 --> 00:18:56,240
Yes, what is it?

310
00:18:56,323 --> 00:18:57,574
Do you have a boyfriend?

311
00:19:01,495 --> 00:19:02,371
I do not.

312
00:19:02,454 --> 00:19:04,539
Why not? You're so pretty.

313
00:19:05,123 --> 00:19:06,124
Your cosmetic surgery…

314
00:19:06,875 --> 00:19:08,335
-It was done really well.
-Hey.

315
00:19:08,919 --> 00:19:11,129
You probably spent
well over ten million won.

316
00:19:11,213 --> 00:19:13,757
Can we see a before photo
to see how well it turned out?

317
00:19:13,840 --> 00:19:16,134
Guys, aren't you curious? Aren't you?

318
00:19:16,218 --> 00:19:19,137
Show us!

319
00:19:19,221 --> 00:19:22,933
Show us!

320
00:19:23,016 --> 00:19:25,602
Show us!

321
00:19:34,653 --> 00:19:35,779
Yes.

322
00:19:35,862 --> 00:19:37,781
I've had cosmetic surgery.

323
00:19:38,907 --> 00:19:40,117
Breast reduction surgery.

324
00:19:41,159 --> 00:19:43,954
I like playing sports,
and they got in the way.

325
00:19:44,830 --> 00:19:46,707
So I got them done.

326
00:19:46,790 --> 00:19:49,126
But it seems

327
00:19:49,209 --> 00:19:54,089
no one in this class needs any reduction,

328
00:19:54,172 --> 00:19:56,675
so I won't take any further questions.

329
00:19:57,592 --> 00:19:59,428
Is she crazy? Who does she think she is?

330
00:19:59,511 --> 00:20:02,389
-So-yeong is so cheeky.
-Let's get back to the lesson.

331
00:20:02,472 --> 00:20:03,890
Before we do that,

332
00:20:03,974 --> 00:20:07,019
I think we need to collect
everyone's phones first.

333
00:20:08,395 --> 00:20:11,231
Everyone, hand in your phones!

334
00:20:11,815 --> 00:20:12,858
She must be crazy.

335
00:20:12,941 --> 00:20:14,109
What does that mean?

336
00:20:14,693 --> 00:20:15,861
Is that a buzzword?

337
00:20:16,361 --> 00:20:19,031
You know I'm not up-to-date
with buzzwords.

338
00:20:19,114 --> 00:20:20,324
Even Reels…

339
00:20:22,159 --> 00:20:23,285
Han Ye-ri.

340
00:20:23,785 --> 00:20:25,704
Hand in your phone.

341
00:20:27,914 --> 00:20:30,292
I'm in the middle of a live stream.

342
00:20:30,959 --> 00:20:35,213
You're new, so you probably haven't heard,
but the principal gave me permission.

343
00:20:38,759 --> 00:20:40,344
This is the last time.

344
00:20:40,969 --> 00:20:44,306
Hand in your phone.

345
00:20:46,433 --> 00:20:52,356
Then do you want to tell my fans yourself?

346
00:20:57,986 --> 00:21:00,030
IS THIS A LIVE BLOOPER?
COME BACK YE-RI

347
00:21:08,038 --> 00:21:09,206
END THE LIVE STREAM?

348
00:21:09,289 --> 00:21:10,165
That scared me.

349
00:21:10,248 --> 00:21:12,209
Are you crazy? What are you doing?

350
00:21:12,292 --> 00:21:14,086
It's the students who are crazy.

351
00:21:14,878 --> 00:21:18,256
The school is much more messed up
than I expected.

352
00:21:18,340 --> 00:21:21,134
Those who act like they're above teachers,

353
00:21:21,218 --> 00:21:23,845
those who treat teachers like toys,

354
00:21:25,138 --> 00:21:27,474
and those who make fools of their teachers

355
00:21:28,225 --> 00:21:32,020
will now be considered
to be in violation of teachers' rights.

356
00:21:32,771 --> 00:21:34,606
I will always accept challenges,

357
00:21:34,689 --> 00:21:37,317
but you must be prepared
to face punishment.

358
00:21:37,401 --> 00:21:38,944
Ms. Im.

359
00:21:39,569 --> 00:21:41,113
Aren't you overreacting?

360
00:21:41,196 --> 00:21:43,323
Let me introduce myself again.

361
00:21:44,241 --> 00:21:47,202
I am Im Han-rim,
an inspector from the ERPB

362
00:21:47,285 --> 00:21:51,081
that operates
under Korea's Ministry of Education.

363
00:21:51,915 --> 00:21:53,667
From this moment on,

364
00:21:53,750 --> 00:21:57,629
I will severely punish
all violations of educational rights

365
00:21:57,712 --> 00:21:59,965
occurring here
at Soyeon Girls' High School.

366
00:22:00,048 --> 00:22:02,592
Then I will destroy
the root causes of it all.

367
00:22:03,260 --> 00:22:07,264
The first step to this is the phones!

368
00:22:07,848 --> 00:22:11,768
Hand over your phones right this second!

369
00:22:34,541 --> 00:22:39,588
I hope what you've just handed in
isn't a second phone or an inactive phone

370
00:22:39,671 --> 00:22:42,466
to fool teachers.

371
00:22:42,549 --> 00:22:44,926
For any students who have done so,

372
00:22:45,010 --> 00:22:47,846
for the final time, I will count to three.

373
00:22:50,765 --> 00:22:51,892
<i>One!</i>

374
00:22:53,059 --> 00:22:54,269
<i>Two!</i>

375
00:22:54,769 --> 00:22:55,979
Three!

376
00:23:03,904 --> 00:23:05,197
PHONE POSSESSION WARNING

377
00:23:19,794 --> 00:23:20,712
<i>Attention students.</i>

378
00:23:20,795 --> 00:23:24,883
<i>There will now be an announcement</i>
<i>of special directives from the ERPB.</i>

379
00:23:27,511 --> 00:23:28,345
<i>First,</i>

380
00:23:29,346 --> 00:23:33,600
<i>Soyeon Girls' High School</i>
<i>now falls under the authority of the ERPB.</i>

381
00:23:36,478 --> 00:23:37,479
<i>Second,</i>

382
00:23:37,562 --> 00:23:41,942
<i>there are no restrictions whatsoever</i>
<i>on the ERPB's teaching methods.</i>

383
00:23:44,444 --> 00:23:45,403
<i>Third,</i>

384
00:23:45,904 --> 00:23:48,448
<i>you must always follow</i>
<i>the inspector's instructions.</i>

385
00:23:50,951 --> 00:23:51,993
<i>Fourth,</i>

386
00:23:52,577 --> 00:23:54,162
<i>in the event of insubordination,</i>

387
00:23:54,246 --> 00:23:57,082
<i>we will not be responsible</i>
<i>for any disadvantages that arise.</i>

388
00:23:57,791 --> 00:23:59,501
TEACHERS' MAIN OFFICE

389
00:24:02,837 --> 00:24:05,006
I'm here from the ERPB.

390
00:24:12,097 --> 00:24:13,515
-Attention!
-Did someone snitch?

391
00:24:14,724 --> 00:24:16,560
"In the event of insubordination,

392
00:24:16,643 --> 00:24:19,354
we won't be responsible
for any disadvantages that arise."

393
00:24:19,938 --> 00:24:21,231
You heard that, right?

394
00:24:21,314 --> 00:24:24,734
Everyone, report to the field!

395
00:24:25,902 --> 00:24:28,280
<i>Please write the details</i>
<i>on the form given to you.</i>

396
00:24:28,363 --> 00:24:32,534
It could be that you were falsely accused,
which led to defamation.

397
00:24:32,617 --> 00:24:34,494
Or maybe you raised this issue,

398
00:24:34,995 --> 00:24:37,956
only to find yourself
being bullied by the students.

399
00:24:38,456 --> 00:24:42,460
Perhaps you're aware of colleagues
who are suffering online

400
00:24:43,336 --> 00:24:47,799
from leaked personal information,
judged appearances, and edited photos.

401
00:24:47,882 --> 00:24:49,426
But you're too scared of the kids,

402
00:24:50,010 --> 00:24:54,806
or maybe you have no choice
and have turned a blind eye.

403
00:24:54,889 --> 00:24:56,391
Whatever it may be,

404
00:24:57,934 --> 00:24:58,810
please tell us.

405
00:25:03,648 --> 00:25:08,945
May I take your silence as consent
to hand over full control to the ERPB?

406
00:25:09,029 --> 00:25:11,698
Pardon? No, it's not that.

407
00:25:11,781 --> 00:25:14,576
It means our school
doesn't have any problems.

408
00:25:15,243 --> 00:25:17,621
If adults fear children,

409
00:25:18,538 --> 00:25:20,206
the world is doomed.

410
00:25:21,082 --> 00:25:24,836
Don't you think it would be even worse
for teachers?

411
00:25:24,919 --> 00:25:27,005
TEACHERS' RIGHTS VIOLATIONS SURVEY

412
00:25:27,088 --> 00:25:27,964
Well…

413
00:25:29,341 --> 00:25:31,009
Please don't think too hard.

414
00:25:31,801 --> 00:25:32,802
It's simple enough.

415
00:25:33,720 --> 00:25:36,222
If you think of anything later,
please write it down

416
00:25:36,306 --> 00:25:38,266
and give it to Inspector Im Han-rim or me.

417
00:25:38,350 --> 00:25:40,810
No chanting on the final repetition!

418
00:25:40,894 --> 00:25:43,188
-Proceed.
-Proceed.

419
00:25:46,775 --> 00:25:48,652
Please hand in the forms to me.

420
00:25:49,152 --> 00:25:51,279
I think that would be best.

421
00:25:53,740 --> 00:25:55,033
Six.

422
00:25:56,993 --> 00:25:58,078
Seven.

423
00:26:00,372 --> 00:26:01,831
Eight.

424
00:26:02,874 --> 00:26:03,833
Hey!

425
00:26:05,752 --> 00:26:06,878
Lift your damn heads up!

426
00:26:09,839 --> 00:26:10,799
One.

427
00:26:10,882 --> 00:26:12,384
SNACK BAR

428
00:26:13,343 --> 00:26:14,511
Unity!

429
00:26:16,054 --> 00:26:17,347
Look at you.

430
00:26:17,931 --> 00:26:19,808
Hey! Unity!

431
00:26:20,767 --> 00:26:21,643
Reporting, sir!

432
00:26:21,726 --> 00:26:25,355
Sergeant First Class, Im Han-rim,
Special Forces Reserve!

433
00:26:25,438 --> 00:26:28,024
I have been assigned
to ERPB duty as of today!

434
00:26:28,108 --> 00:26:28,983
Unity!

435
00:26:29,067 --> 00:26:31,444
What's with the report between civilians?
At ease.

436
00:26:32,278 --> 00:26:33,571
Even so!

437
00:26:34,406 --> 00:26:35,240
Unity!

438
00:26:38,993 --> 00:26:40,078
Hey.

439
00:26:40,161 --> 00:26:41,329
My goodness.

440
00:26:41,413 --> 00:26:43,915
Hey, your disguise is great, Im Han-rim.

441
00:26:43,998 --> 00:26:45,375
No, don't. It's embarrassing.

442
00:26:45,458 --> 00:26:48,503
You haven't met yet, have you?

443
00:26:48,586 --> 00:26:49,587
Come here.

444
00:26:49,671 --> 00:26:52,549
This is Deputy Director Bong Geun-dae.

445
00:26:52,632 --> 00:26:53,967
It's "Deputy Bong" for short.

446
00:26:55,176 --> 00:26:56,344
Deputy Bong.

447
00:26:57,220 --> 00:26:58,555
He's not just any deputy.

448
00:26:59,055 --> 00:27:02,642
You know KAIST, right?
He graduated from there in just two years.

449
00:27:02,726 --> 00:27:04,018
Wow, is that right?

450
00:27:05,061 --> 00:27:08,106
Nice to meet you.
I served in the same unit as Hwa-jin.

451
00:27:09,482 --> 00:27:10,567
Right…

452
00:27:11,484 --> 00:27:12,694
My name is Bong Geun-dae.

453
00:27:15,029 --> 00:27:16,114
What is it?

454
00:27:16,197 --> 00:27:17,449
What? What is it?

455
00:27:18,324 --> 00:27:20,452
I was sizing him up,
as it's our first meeting.

456
00:27:22,162 --> 00:27:25,039
Just be understanding, Deputy Bong.
She's a bit of a nutcase.

457
00:27:30,754 --> 00:27:32,338
So when will you tell me?

458
00:27:32,422 --> 00:27:33,631
Tell you what?

459
00:27:33,715 --> 00:27:37,594
You said you'd tell me why you hired me
once I started work.

460
00:27:37,677 --> 00:27:39,429
I just did. Because you're a nutcase.

461
00:27:39,512 --> 00:27:41,431
Is that really all?

462
00:27:45,727 --> 00:27:46,728
Here's a question.

463
00:27:47,812 --> 00:27:51,357
Kids are getting more cunning
and doing things that defy common sense.

464
00:27:51,441 --> 00:27:52,275
What should we do?

465
00:27:52,358 --> 00:27:54,402
Beat a nutcase with a nutcase. Am I right?

466
00:27:54,486 --> 00:27:55,320
That's right!

467
00:27:55,403 --> 00:27:57,238
Here, anything crazy goes!

468
00:27:57,322 --> 00:28:00,283
I like that a lot!

469
00:28:01,826 --> 00:28:02,702
However,

470
00:28:03,787 --> 00:28:05,789
remember one thing.

471
00:28:07,957 --> 00:28:10,251
You can't kill anyone. All right?

472
00:28:10,335 --> 00:28:11,920
If you feel the urge,

473
00:28:12,003 --> 00:28:16,758
write the Chinese character for "patience"
on your palm three times.

474
00:28:18,259 --> 00:28:19,093
Understood, sir.

475
00:28:20,261 --> 00:28:22,722
Is this the correct Chinese character
for "patience"?

476
00:28:23,473 --> 00:28:25,141
That's "benevolence."

477
00:28:25,725 --> 00:28:27,519
Maybe you need a little benevolence.

478
00:28:27,602 --> 00:28:30,980
I know. Deputy Bong, you should teach her
how to write "patience."

479
00:28:31,064 --> 00:28:33,274
There's a lot you can learn from him.

480
00:28:33,775 --> 00:28:34,609
Try writing it.

481
00:28:37,946 --> 00:28:38,780
Well…

482
00:28:40,114 --> 00:28:40,949
PATIENCE

483
00:28:41,032 --> 00:28:44,285
"Cut your heart with a knife."

484
00:28:44,369 --> 00:28:47,288
This is how I memorized it for exams.

485
00:28:47,372 --> 00:28:49,541
Cut out the hearts of enemies!

486
00:28:51,209 --> 00:28:52,794
I've learned it. Thank you.

487
00:28:57,966 --> 00:28:58,842
Let's get to work.

488
00:28:59,968 --> 00:29:01,636
I'll do what I always do. Unity!

489
00:29:02,387 --> 00:29:04,305
-No more saluting.
-Understood, sir.

490
00:29:05,014 --> 00:29:06,140
I like your ribbon.

491
00:29:06,224 --> 00:29:07,851
Right. Damn it.

492
00:29:11,938 --> 00:29:12,772
Deputy Bong.

493
00:29:15,608 --> 00:29:17,360
It's Deputy Director Bong Geun-dae.

494
00:29:17,443 --> 00:29:20,905
Do you know the most dangerous place
in a girls' high school?

495
00:29:22,031 --> 00:29:23,074
No.

496
00:29:30,081 --> 00:29:31,291
It's right here.

497
00:29:32,458 --> 00:29:33,960
The snack bar.

498
00:29:35,086 --> 00:29:38,172
What's so dangerous about a snack bar?

499
00:29:40,717 --> 00:29:41,551
Work hard.

500
00:30:02,113 --> 00:30:04,908
Slow down!

501
00:30:06,284 --> 00:30:07,452
Move!

502
00:30:09,537 --> 00:30:10,788
No!

503
00:30:12,624 --> 00:30:15,168
Wait. You can't just open them
and eat them like that.

504
00:30:15,668 --> 00:30:17,211
Guys, you've got to pay!

505
00:30:17,295 --> 00:30:19,005
Pay up!

506
00:30:28,389 --> 00:30:30,475
Where are you all going right now?

507
00:30:30,558 --> 00:30:31,851
Class is finished.

508
00:30:31,935 --> 00:30:33,519
You still have afternoon homeroom.

509
00:30:34,395 --> 00:30:35,605
That's not a thing here.

510
00:30:35,688 --> 00:30:36,814
What about cleaning?

511
00:30:43,154 --> 00:30:45,406
Our teacher told us not to.

512
00:30:46,115 --> 00:30:47,408
She said she'd do it.

513
00:30:50,787 --> 00:30:51,746
Didn't you?

514
00:30:52,956 --> 00:30:55,041
Well, I…

515
00:30:59,087 --> 00:31:01,881
Did you not see the special directives?

516
00:31:02,757 --> 00:31:05,218
If you mess with the inspector,
you're dead.

517
00:31:05,843 --> 00:31:07,178
Damn it.

518
00:31:09,138 --> 00:31:12,350
The people who use the space
are responsible for cleaning it.

519
00:31:17,814 --> 00:31:18,815
All right.

520
00:31:19,440 --> 00:31:21,442
No one is exempt.

521
00:31:21,526 --> 00:31:24,612
Today, we will begin "keeping house."

522
00:31:24,696 --> 00:31:27,573
-What is "keeping house"?
-Desks and chairs to the back.

523
00:31:28,074 --> 00:31:29,117
All the way back.

524
00:31:33,621 --> 00:31:35,623
All the way!

525
00:31:42,714 --> 00:31:46,926
Scrub the floors
until you can see your reflection.

526
00:31:54,475 --> 00:31:55,601
My socks…

527
00:31:58,354 --> 00:32:00,773
Ms. Im, are you sure this will be okay?

528
00:32:00,857 --> 00:32:03,359
The parents may protest…

529
00:32:14,746 --> 00:32:17,915
AFTER THE KO YEONG-SU INCIDENT,
SHE BECAME OUR TEACHER TO TORMENT US

530
00:32:17,999 --> 00:32:19,625
AND NOW SHE HAS CALLED ON THE ERPB

531
00:32:19,709 --> 00:32:21,794
WE'RE ALL BEING FRAMED,
INCLUDING POOR YE-RI

532
00:32:30,178 --> 00:32:32,305
MINISTRY OF EDUCATION

533
00:32:40,688 --> 00:32:41,814
Hey!

534
00:32:42,315 --> 00:32:44,776
-Great work, sir!
-Great work today.

535
00:32:44,859 --> 00:32:48,279
I told you no saluting. We're civilians.

536
00:32:48,362 --> 00:32:49,572
Understood, sir.

537
00:32:49,655 --> 00:32:51,074
-Is this what I asked for?
-Yes.

538
00:32:51,574 --> 00:32:52,784
Anything noteworthy?

539
00:32:52,867 --> 00:32:55,453
-Well, my hand is…
-I was about to report to you.

540
00:32:56,162 --> 00:32:58,206
I think Ms. Jung is really scared.

541
00:32:58,289 --> 00:33:01,250
She was worried and asked
if it was okay to continue this.

542
00:33:01,334 --> 00:33:03,544
I'll meet with Ms. Jung.

543
00:33:03,628 --> 00:33:07,924
You check every student's social media
at the school.

544
00:33:08,007 --> 00:33:09,842
Find any slander about the teachers.

545
00:33:11,719 --> 00:33:12,595
You mean me, sir?

546
00:33:12,678 --> 00:33:14,305
-Why? Don't you want to?
-Yes, I do.

547
00:33:14,388 --> 00:33:15,890
All right. Good luck with it.

548
00:33:15,973 --> 00:33:17,141
But my hand…

549
00:33:22,814 --> 00:33:23,689
Good luck.

550
00:33:26,901 --> 00:33:28,194
Deputy Bong.

551
00:33:30,488 --> 00:33:31,531
Deputy Director Bong.

552
00:33:35,034 --> 00:33:35,868
Yes?

553
00:33:38,246 --> 00:33:42,708
I believe work is only done efficiently
with a command structure.

554
00:33:42,792 --> 00:33:44,961
You can just stay there and talk.

555
00:33:46,921 --> 00:33:49,132
I'm saying
there should be a chain of command.

556
00:33:50,174 --> 00:33:51,008
Right.

557
00:33:51,092 --> 00:33:52,802
Right. What grade?

558
00:33:53,386 --> 00:33:54,220
Pardon?

559
00:33:54,303 --> 00:33:55,638
What grade are you?

560
00:33:55,721 --> 00:33:58,057
I'm Grade Five…

561
00:33:59,976 --> 00:34:00,810
I'm Grade One.

562
00:34:01,644 --> 00:34:03,229
I'm a higher grade, and I'm older,

563
00:34:03,312 --> 00:34:06,440
so I hope you'll follow
my instructions carefully.

564
00:34:06,524 --> 00:34:09,193
I ask that you monitor
all the students' social media.

565
00:34:09,277 --> 00:34:10,611
Every single student.

566
00:34:11,279 --> 00:34:12,655
Right now?

567
00:34:16,325 --> 00:34:17,827
By the end of the day.

568
00:34:20,163 --> 00:34:21,747
Grade Five? What's wrong with you?

569
00:34:23,916 --> 00:34:24,917
You haven't served.

570
00:34:27,044 --> 00:34:28,671
Let me know when you're done!

571
00:34:57,283 --> 00:35:00,119
I'm sorry.
I'd like the class for a moment.

572
00:35:07,710 --> 00:35:09,045
Do you recognize these?

573
00:35:09,962 --> 00:35:12,381
They're photos you posted on social media

574
00:35:12,465 --> 00:35:15,343
that were taken illegally and then edited

575
00:35:15,843 --> 00:35:17,428
to mock your teachers.

576
00:35:17,929 --> 00:35:21,682
These prove you spread false information
with malicious intent.

577
00:35:22,183 --> 00:35:25,770
This is a criminal act
that constitutes defamation.

578
00:35:26,520 --> 00:35:28,272
From now on,

579
00:35:28,356 --> 00:35:32,151
the ERPB will crack down
on online violations of teachers' rights.

580
00:35:33,736 --> 00:35:34,737
By the way,

581
00:35:34,820 --> 00:35:38,074
isn't going through our social media
a violation of human rights?

582
00:35:38,157 --> 00:35:40,159
Yeah, this is a human rights violation.

583
00:35:40,243 --> 00:35:43,496
I'm asking whether the ERPB has
that kind of authority.

584
00:35:47,208 --> 00:35:51,712
If you want to know about our authority,
I suggest you visit the ERPB website,

585
00:35:52,213 --> 00:35:55,341
go to "Bureau Introduction,"
and then "Grounds of Establishment."

586
00:35:55,424 --> 00:35:57,343
There, under "Legal Documents,"

587
00:35:57,426 --> 00:36:01,305
you will see the ERPB Establishment Act,
where you can read Article 8.

588
00:36:03,015 --> 00:36:04,183
All right, then.

589
00:36:04,267 --> 00:36:09,438
Those whose names are called,
report to the field!

590
00:36:09,522 --> 00:36:11,732
Stay in formation.

591
00:36:11,816 --> 00:36:12,900
Stay in formation.

592
00:36:12,984 --> 00:36:15,278
Left flank, march forward!

593
00:36:15,361 --> 00:36:17,405
Left flank!

594
00:36:17,488 --> 00:36:19,490
<i>This is so annoying, seriously!</i>

595
00:36:19,573 --> 00:36:20,783
My legs hurt so damn much.

596
00:36:21,284 --> 00:36:23,411
Hey, who the hell called in the ERPB?

597
00:36:23,494 --> 00:36:24,954
Isn't it obvious?

598
00:36:25,454 --> 00:36:28,249
It's the teachers calling in the ERPB
to back them up.

599
00:36:28,833 --> 00:36:30,501
I don't think so.

600
00:36:33,004 --> 00:36:33,879
What?

601
00:36:33,963 --> 00:36:36,757
Why else would they have come?
There's no reason.

602
00:36:36,841 --> 00:36:39,135
It could be because of Mr. Ko.

603
00:36:40,219 --> 00:36:42,805
Honestly, we all know
he wouldn't do something like that.

604
00:36:42,888 --> 00:36:45,141
And it's not like anyone saw it happen.

605
00:36:49,437 --> 00:36:52,606
Did you guys see it?
Did you see Mr. Ko with Ye-ri?

606
00:36:52,690 --> 00:36:54,442
What are you all talking about?

607
00:36:56,152 --> 00:36:57,278
Is it about me?

608
00:37:00,448 --> 00:37:04,035
We were talking about the ERPB,
wondering when they'd get lost.

609
00:37:06,078 --> 00:37:07,371
It must be hard on you.

610
00:37:07,455 --> 00:37:10,458
They'll be leaving soon enough.
Don't worry about it.

611
00:37:10,958 --> 00:37:11,792
Let's go.

612
00:37:12,877 --> 00:37:14,337
-Let's go.
-Let's go.

613
00:37:21,594 --> 00:37:23,512
HAN YE-RI: GUESS WHO LIVES HERE?

614
00:37:23,596 --> 00:37:25,931
ISN'T THAT YE-RI'S HOMEROOM TEACHER
BACK THERE?

615
00:37:27,475 --> 00:37:30,895
THIS IS SURYEON VILLA NEAR MY PLACE!

616
00:37:46,619 --> 00:37:48,412
MISANG HAGWON

617
00:37:48,496 --> 00:37:49,830
RÉSUMÉ

618
00:37:51,999 --> 00:37:53,876
Are you really thinking of quitting?

619
00:37:53,959 --> 00:37:56,420
There's so much to think about
in a school.

620
00:37:56,504 --> 00:38:00,174
You're dealing with everything
from student support to paperwork.

621
00:38:00,674 --> 00:38:03,260
But in a <i>hagwon,</i>

622
00:38:03,803 --> 00:38:06,555
I feel like you can just focus
on the lessons.

623
00:38:06,639 --> 00:38:08,182
I'm a little surprised.

624
00:38:08,265 --> 00:38:10,434
Our friends made a bet

625
00:38:10,518 --> 00:38:12,853
on which of us would become principal.

626
00:38:12,937 --> 00:38:15,689
You were the clear winner, Seon-yeong.

627
00:38:16,440 --> 00:38:17,983
Yeah, I know.

628
00:38:20,569 --> 00:38:24,657
Well, I thought I'd try enjoying life.

629
00:38:30,663 --> 00:38:34,500
There are many Soyeon Girls' High students
who come to our <i>hagwon.</i>

630
00:38:34,583 --> 00:38:36,627
I did hear about you too.

631
00:38:37,128 --> 00:38:40,881
<i>Hagwons </i>and schools are all the same.
It's not easy here either.

632
00:38:40,965 --> 00:38:43,175
And you've always been tough.

633
00:38:43,676 --> 00:38:45,845
If you really can't take it anymore,
come back.

634
00:38:46,345 --> 00:38:47,721
Let's talk again then.

635
00:38:50,516 --> 00:38:52,184
Okay.

636
00:39:02,945 --> 00:39:04,196
Hello.

637
00:39:15,541 --> 00:39:17,293
-Ms. Jung.
-Yes?

638
00:39:17,376 --> 00:39:20,379
I've been solving problems,
but I'm stuck on one.

639
00:39:20,963 --> 00:39:21,881
Let's see.

640
00:39:22,381 --> 00:39:23,799
It's question 18.

641
00:39:23,883 --> 00:39:26,051
I just don't get
why the answer is number three.

642
00:39:26,635 --> 00:39:28,179
Oh, this one?

643
00:39:28,888 --> 00:39:32,892
You need to know the definition
of "combination" to solve this.

644
00:39:33,392 --> 00:39:35,603
Here, 50 choose k equals

645
00:39:35,686 --> 00:39:40,941
50 factorial over k factorial multiplied
by 50 minus k factorial…

646
00:39:45,237 --> 00:39:46,697
So the answer is number three.

647
00:39:48,199 --> 00:39:49,700
This was so confusing.

648
00:39:50,493 --> 00:39:53,287
But you've made it easier to understand.

649
00:39:53,370 --> 00:39:55,456
I should've come to see you earlier.

650
00:39:55,539 --> 00:39:57,416
-Thank you, Ms. Jung.
-Sure.

651
00:39:58,876 --> 00:40:02,421
If I get stuck solving problems again,

652
00:40:02,922 --> 00:40:04,507
could I ask you again?

653
00:40:06,217 --> 00:40:07,134
Yes, of course.

654
00:40:08,344 --> 00:40:09,595
Thank you.

655
00:40:13,057 --> 00:40:13,974
Hello.

656
00:40:20,147 --> 00:40:22,608
So what we learned in the last class is…

657
00:40:22,691 --> 00:40:24,193
Conditional probability.

658
00:40:28,197 --> 00:40:29,031
Yes.

659
00:40:29,573 --> 00:40:33,202
We'll use conditional probability
to solve this problem.

660
00:40:33,285 --> 00:40:37,122
If we choose only natural numbers that are
multiples of two, from one to twelve,

661
00:40:37,206 --> 00:40:38,791
then P(A) would be…

662
00:40:38,874 --> 00:40:40,834
Six over twelve.

663
00:40:43,462 --> 00:40:44,463
Right.

664
00:40:45,130 --> 00:40:47,216
That's right. It's six over twelve.

665
00:40:47,967 --> 00:40:49,718
And P(B) is…

666
00:40:49,802 --> 00:40:51,929
Four over twelve.

667
00:40:52,513 --> 00:40:55,140
The probability of A and B is…

668
00:40:55,224 --> 00:40:56,350
Two over twelve.

669
00:40:56,934 --> 00:40:59,144
Shall we try to solve question two
the same way?

670
00:40:59,228 --> 00:41:01,105
Yes, ma'am.

671
00:41:01,188 --> 00:41:02,940
-Who wants to try?
-Kang Min-seo does.

672
00:41:03,023 --> 00:41:04,608
Jin Sang-hui does.

673
00:41:05,818 --> 00:41:06,652
-Min-seo?
-Yes.

674
00:41:06,735 --> 00:41:08,028
-Do you want to try?
-Try it.

675
00:41:08,112 --> 00:41:10,155
Okay. Come up and have a go, Min-seo.

676
00:41:15,202 --> 00:41:16,203
Ms. Jung!

677
00:41:17,288 --> 00:41:19,707
Today's lesson was the best!
I really enjoyed it.

678
00:41:19,790 --> 00:41:21,125
You were epic today.

679
00:41:23,294 --> 00:41:24,211
You're the best!

680
00:41:25,337 --> 00:41:26,297
Ms. Jung.

681
00:41:31,760 --> 00:41:33,679
You must not be so easily swayed.

682
00:41:33,762 --> 00:41:36,807
She's cunning
and may just be gaslighting you.

683
00:41:37,725 --> 00:41:39,351
It'd be best to keep your guard up.

684
00:41:41,770 --> 00:41:43,022
I'm aware of it too.

685
00:41:45,232 --> 00:41:48,277
Whether this is real or just an act,

686
00:41:48,986 --> 00:41:51,363
they're still changing.

687
00:41:53,532 --> 00:41:55,451
I'm so grateful to the ERPB

688
00:41:56,035 --> 00:41:58,120
for even getting us this far.

689
00:41:59,496 --> 00:42:00,623
Thank you.

690
00:42:16,764 --> 00:42:17,681
Ms. Jung.

691
00:42:19,350 --> 00:42:21,685
Ye-ri, what brings you here?

692
00:42:21,769 --> 00:42:24,021
You're probably wondering
why I'm being so nice.

693
00:42:25,230 --> 00:42:29,234
I've wanted to get to know you better
for a while now.

694
00:42:29,318 --> 00:42:31,945
But I felt like
you had the wrong idea about me.

695
00:42:32,529 --> 00:42:34,990
And I didn't know where to start
to clear it up.

696
00:42:35,991 --> 00:42:37,326
So it took me a while.

697
00:42:38,535 --> 00:42:39,453
I'm sorry.

698
00:42:41,413 --> 00:42:42,998
On that note,

699
00:42:43,082 --> 00:42:45,626
how does live streaming sound?

700
00:42:46,835 --> 00:42:47,878
Live streaming?

701
00:42:47,961 --> 00:42:51,507
I want to let people know
that we're on good terms again,

702
00:42:51,590 --> 00:42:55,344
and wouldn't it clear up
some of the misunderstandings about you?

703
00:42:59,723 --> 00:43:01,725
STUDY PLAN

704
00:43:06,105 --> 00:43:07,981
YEAR 3, CLASS 4, HAN YE-RI

705
00:43:09,566 --> 00:43:10,651
<i>And in return,</i>

706
00:43:10,734 --> 00:43:14,154
it would be good
if you could speak a bit about the ERPB.

707
00:43:14,947 --> 00:43:15,781
Sorry?

708
00:43:16,365 --> 00:43:18,826
Everyone is having a real hard time
because of it.

709
00:43:18,909 --> 00:43:21,120
They keep asking me for help.

710
00:43:22,454 --> 00:43:25,290
Don't you think they'd love it
if you helped too?

711
00:43:36,927 --> 00:43:37,928
Ms. Jung.

712
00:43:39,722 --> 00:43:42,349
Have you ever cut class before?

713
00:43:43,517 --> 00:43:44,351
Pardon?

714
00:43:44,893 --> 00:43:46,562
Cut class?

715
00:43:55,529 --> 00:43:57,781
My goodness, they're so precious.

716
00:43:57,865 --> 00:43:58,782
Aren't they?

717
00:43:59,366 --> 00:44:01,785
Makes you wonder
where those monstrous kids come from.

718
00:44:03,620 --> 00:44:06,540
What is it that you wanted to say?

719
00:44:08,041 --> 00:44:10,502
How much longer
are you going to put up with this?

720
00:44:11,378 --> 00:44:12,796
Isn't it about time this ended?

721
00:44:19,052 --> 00:44:20,137
ALL THE DOGS FORUM

722
00:44:21,972 --> 00:44:23,348
SCHOOLS THESE DAYS… OMG

723
00:44:23,432 --> 00:44:24,767
Take a look at this.

724
00:44:26,143 --> 00:44:28,187
It's a picture of me that Ye-ri posted.

725
00:44:28,687 --> 00:44:31,356
Time and time again,
I report it, and it gets removed,

726
00:44:31,440 --> 00:44:33,525
but it shows up again somewhere else.

727
00:44:34,026 --> 00:44:38,071
In the end, I'll just get branded
as that kind of person.

728
00:44:38,155 --> 00:44:40,365
I have to live the rest of my life

729
00:44:41,325 --> 00:44:47,122
proving I'm really not that kind of person
and that things weren't as they seemed.

730
00:44:47,623 --> 00:44:50,501
And when I get tired of it,

731
00:44:52,169 --> 00:44:53,337
I'll probably end up

732
00:44:54,254 --> 00:44:56,006
like Mr. Ko.

733
00:45:03,013 --> 00:45:05,098
I'm afraid of the students.

734
00:45:06,016 --> 00:45:09,311
Just seeing Ye-ri's hand on her phone
makes my heart pound.

735
00:45:14,107 --> 00:45:17,653
My fiancée was a teacher.

736
00:45:19,655 --> 00:45:21,073
Two years ago…

737
00:45:24,827 --> 00:45:28,539
she lost her life
at the hands of a student she taught.

738
00:45:31,792 --> 00:45:33,585
<i>We'll start your photo session.</i>

739
00:45:33,669 --> 00:45:35,796
Okay. Bride, you're looking great.

740
00:45:36,296 --> 00:45:37,464
Okay.

741
00:45:37,548 --> 00:45:39,967
Groom, you should look at the bride too.

742
00:45:40,050 --> 00:45:41,927
-Right.
-That's great.

743
00:45:42,010 --> 00:45:43,971
Groom, hold your arm higher.

744
00:46:54,791 --> 00:46:55,709
Ga-yun.

745
00:46:59,421 --> 00:47:00,964
Ga-yun, I'm here.

746
00:47:32,746 --> 00:47:34,456
Thank you for waiting for me.

747
00:48:10,867 --> 00:48:14,079
So I truly understand
the fear you're feeling

748
00:48:14,162 --> 00:48:17,624
after what happened to Mr. Ko.

749
00:48:19,418 --> 00:48:21,545
But that's why I am asking this of you.

750
00:48:22,045 --> 00:48:24,006
It's not for your sake.

751
00:48:25,674 --> 00:48:28,844
It's for the sake of the kids you teach.

752
00:48:36,810 --> 00:48:38,020
Ms. Jung.

753
00:48:38,562 --> 00:48:40,605
Why do you think we came here?

754
00:48:42,941 --> 00:48:43,942
Of course,

755
00:48:44,484 --> 00:48:46,945
because of Mr. Ko…

756
00:48:47,029 --> 00:48:48,947
No, we are here because of you.

757
00:48:53,577 --> 00:48:57,414
The kids requested that we save you.

758
00:48:59,124 --> 00:49:00,542
Year 3, class 4.

759
00:49:01,626 --> 00:49:04,337
They're students in your homeroom class.

760
00:49:06,006 --> 00:49:07,966
REPORTS RELATED TO SOYEON GIRLS' HIGH

761
00:49:08,050 --> 00:49:13,221
<i>Hello. I am Park Su-jin,</i>
<i>a student at Soyeon Girls' High School.</i>

762
00:49:13,305 --> 00:49:14,681
<i>When I saw strange rumors</i>

763
00:49:14,765 --> 00:49:18,643
<i>and slanderous posts spreading</i>
<i>about our homeroom teacher,</i>

764
00:49:18,727 --> 00:49:22,564
<i>I was so upset and angry</i>
<i>that I decided to write this letter.</i>

765
00:49:22,647 --> 00:49:26,443
<i>After a post was shared</i>
<i>claiming Ms. Jung wasn't teaching,</i>

766
00:49:26,526 --> 00:49:28,862
<i>the whole school fell into chaos.</i>

767
00:49:28,945 --> 00:49:30,864
<i>But the claim just isn't true.</i>

768
00:49:30,947 --> 00:49:35,118
<i>We want to see her teach</i>
<i>with full passion again, like before.</i>

769
00:49:35,202 --> 00:49:38,371
<i>Please protect</i>
<i>Ms. Jung's honor and rights.</i>

770
00:49:38,872 --> 00:49:43,543
<i>Please take this situation seriously</i>
<i>and protect teachers like Ms. Jung,</i>

771
00:49:43,627 --> 00:49:46,588
<i>who quietly devote themselves</i>
